  "body": "This breaks code like:\n\n```\nstruct Struct {\n    f: String,\n    g: String,\n}\n\nimpl Drop for Struct { ... }\n\nfn main() {\n    let x = Struct { ... };\n    drop(x);\n    x.f = ...;\n}\n```\n\nChange this code to not create partially-initialized structures. For\nexample:\n\n```\nstruct Struct {\n    f: String,\n    g: String,\n}\n\nimpl Drop for Struct { ... }\n\nfn main() {\n    let x = Struct { ... };\n    drop(x);\n    x = Struct {\n        f: ...,\n        g: ...,\n    }\n}\n```\n\nCloses #18571.\n\n[breaking-change]\n\nI suspect I may have missed some cases that I should have checked.\n\nr? @nikomatsakis\n",
